The paper proposes a new sampling strategy for compressive hyperspectral imaging using dictionary learning and singular value decomposition. This involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) for compressive sensing, computer vision (cs.CV) for hyperspectral imaging, machine learning (cs.LG) for dictionary learning, and mathematical modeling (cs.MM) for SVD. Additionally, the paper discusses matrix balancing (cs.SI) as a method for improving reconstruction performance.
